                },
                "description": {
                    "chat": "",
                    "unidentified": "",
                    "value": "<p>The haunt causes a living creature in the room to experience a full elven life, weathering every wound, misfortune, loss, and consequence of aging centuries in a matter of seconds. The target must attempt a <span data-pf2-saving-throw=\"fortitude\" data-pf2-dc=\"38\" data-pf2-traits=\"mental,occult\" data-pf2-label=\"Live a Thousand Lives DC\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">Fortitude</span> save.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Critical Success</strong>: The target is unaffected.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong>: The target becomes @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Fatigued]{Fatigued}.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong>: The target becomes @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Drained]{Drained} 1 (or its drained value increases by 1, to a maximum of drained 3), and it is @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Paralyzed]{Paralyzed} until the end of its next turn.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong>: As failure, but the target also becomes @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Doomed]{Doomed} 1 (or its doomed value increases by 1).</p>"
                },
